    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="809"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d809">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">892.014/6–1946: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Siam</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Yost</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-19">June 19,
                            1946</date>.<lb/>[Received June 19—6:56 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>692. Govt yesterday sought and obtained from joint session Parliament by vote 122
                    to 4 authority to submit Indochina frontier question to UN and accept in advance
                    obligations of pacific settlement stipulated Article 35 Charter. Govt made clear
                    decision by UN regarding <pb facs="1037" n="1025" xml:id="pg_1025"/> either
                    frontier incidents or disputed territories would be binding on Siam, and
                    Parliament, with this understanding, approved submission of either or both
                    questions UN. Prime Minister announced Siamese delegation proceeding shortly to
                    UN headquarters and asked opposition participate in delegation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Yost</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
